Body:
Description: File System Copy Action - When copying files from source to destination files are created in a fsam.tmp folder at the same level as the target. Every 1-2 mins the files are written, then deleted from the .tmp with no files winding up in the destination. No files exist prior to action. 
This happens with overwrite, terminate, retry and batching options on and off.
What We've Learned Updated: USA TZ

Hey @Nicholas Zimmer​ ,
